{"title_page": "Promi Big Brother (season 2)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television season\n| season_number        = 2\n| bgcolour             = #33C6B7\n| image                = Promi Big Brother 2012.jpg\n| module1              = {{Infobox reality competition season\n| presenter            = [[Jochen Schropp]]\n| num_days             = 17\n| num_contestants      = 12\n| winner               = Aaron Troschke\n| runner_up            = Claudia Effenberg\n| companion_shows      = {{Plainlist|\n* ''Promi Big Brother \u2013 Die Late Night Show''\n* ''Promi Big Brother \u2013 Die Webshow''\n}}\n}}\n| country              = Germany\n| num_episodes         = 15\n| network              = [[Sat.1]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2014|8|15|df=y}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2014|8|29|df=y}}\n}}\n\nThe second series of ''[[Big Brother Germany|Promi Big Brother]]'' started on 15 August 2014 and ended on 29 August 2014. It is the second series of the [[Big Brother (TV series)|Big Brother franchise]] on [[Sat.1]], after it left [[RTL II]]. Twelve celebrity housemates (\"promis\") entered the house on Day 1. The show is hosted by Jochen Schropp.<ref>http://www.sat1.de/tv/promi-big-brother/news/die-marke-big-brother-ist-zurueck-im-deutschen-fernsehen</ref>\n\n== Format ==\nPromis had participated in tasks and matches for treats or to avoid punishments. Daily nominations also took place (from Day 8 to 14). Furthermore, the house consists of two floors, the upper luxury floor and the lower poverty floor. Housemates on the luxury floor choose of the poor housemates to join them upstairs, whilst the public will vote one of the 7 downstairs.\n\n==House==\nThis year's ''Promi Big Brother'' contains two floors, each floor having its separate living areas, bathrooms, bedrooms and diary rooms. The upper floor is luxurious, whilst the lower floor is meager with no beds or real seatings.\n\n== Promis ==\nOriginally seven celebrity housemates entered upstairs on Day 3, whilst other five entered downstairs two days earlier (Day 1).\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; line-height:20px; width:auto;\" \n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Celebrity\n!scope=\"col\" | Age on entry\n!scope=\"col\" | Notability\n!scope=\"col\" | Day entered\n!scope=\"col\" | Day exited\n!scope=\"col\" | Status\n|-\n| Aaron Troschke\n| 24\n| Famous quiz contestant and media personality <small>(heritage from [[Russia]])</small>\n| 1\n| 17\n| {{won|Winner}}\n|-\n| [[:de:Claudia Effenberg|Claudia Effenberg]]\n| 49\n| Model/footballer's wife\n| 3\n| 17\n| {{Runner-up}}\n|-\n| [[Ronald Schill]]\n| 55\n| Former politician and judge\n| 3\n| 17\n| {{CFinalist|Third place}}\n|-\n| [[:de:Paul Janke|Paul Janke]]\n| 30\n| Reality TV star (''The Bachelor'')\n| 1\n| 17\n| {{CFinalist|Fourth place}}\n|-\n| [[Michael Wendler]]\n| 42\n| Singer\n| 3\n| 17\n| {{CFinalist|Fifth place}}\n|-\n| [[Hubert Kah]]\n| 55\n| 80es pop icon\n| 3\n| 16\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|-\n| [[:de:Alexandra Rietz|Alexandra Rietz]]\n| 43\n| Scripted crime series actress\n| 1\n| 15\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|-\n| Mia Julia Br\u00fcckner\n| 27\n| Porn star / Ballermann performer\n| 1\n| 14\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|-\n| [[:de:Liz Baffoe|Liz Baffoe]]\n| 44\n| Soap actress <small>(heritage from [[Ghana]])</small>\n| 3\n| 13\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|-\n| Ela Tas\n| 22\n| Reality TV contestant <small>(heritage from [[Turkey]])</small>\n| 3\n| 12\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|-\n| Mario-Max Prinz zu Schaumburg-Lippe\n| 36\n| Royalty <small>(originally from [[Austria]])</small>\n| 3\n| 11\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|-\n| Janina Youssefian\n| 33\n| Model <small>(heritage from [[Iran]])</small>\n| 1\n| 10\n| {{eliminated|Evicted}}\n|}\n\n== Nominations table ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:85%; line-height:15px; width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:6%;\" colspan=2|\n! style=\"width:6%;\" | {{nowrap|Day 10}}\n! style=\"width:6%;\" | {{nowrap|Day 11}}\n! style=\"width:6%;\"